# GC Praesidium community

This repository accompanies the **GC-arc (Germinal Centre governance) series**, a sequence of
conceptual and mathematical papers developing a **capacity-limited governance framework** for
adaptive immune systems.

The series culminates in **GC-arc7**, which introduces **oligoclonal capture** as a distinct
failure mode of germinal-centre regulation, with implications for immune stability, chronic
disease, and global health.

All papers are archived on Zenodo with permanent DOIs.

---

## GC-arc7 (current paper)

**Oligoclonal Capture as a Failure Mode of Governance in Adaptive Systems:  
Implications for Immune Stability, Chronic Disease, and Global Health**

James Sutton (2025-2026)

ðŸ“„ Zenodo: https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.18163641

GC-arc7 synthesises experimental immunology, Bayesian inference, and capacity-limited dynamical
systems to propose that certain chronic immune pathologies arise not from excessive activation
or defective tolerance alone, but from **collapse of comparative selection and recoverability**
under finite regulatory capacity.

