germinal-centre governance failure to chronic immune disease and public-health fragility.

---

## Scope and positioning

- The GC-arc series is **independent of the GQR/QGE programme**.
- All mathematics used here is **classical**, drawing on dynamical systems, control theory,
  and Bayesian inference.
- The novelty lies in **importing ridge-structured, capacity-limited governance concepts into
  immunology**, particularly in the context of somatic hypermutation and germinal-centre dynamics.

---

## Intended audience

- Immunologists and clinician-scientists
- Systems biologists
- Researchers studying chronic immune disease, relapse, and recovery
- Readers interested in governance and stability of adaptive biological systems

---

